Valhalla ("Hall of the slain") is Odin'sValhalla ("Hall of the slain") is Odin's&nbsp;hall, the home for the einherjaar who died gloriously in battle. 
It has five hundred and forty doors, and through each of them, eight hundred men can march abreast, indicating the size of the hall, as well as the numbers of the einherjaar. Its walls are made of spears, the roof made of shields and benches covered with armors.
When he visits Asgard, Tyr dwells within it as well. 

